name: Scyther
flavorText: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Slashing Strike.

name: Pineco
flavorText: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.

name: Seedot
flavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Nuzleaf
flavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Shiftry
flavorText: A Pokemon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.
Attack1Text: Choose 3 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. If you do, shuffle all of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that you didn't choose, and all cards attached to those Pokemon, into their deck.
Attack2Text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Shroomish
flavorText: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Breloom
flavorText: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Roselia
flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Roserade
flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Grotle
flavorText: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Torterra ex
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Grass Pokemon in play.
Attack2Text: Heal 50 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Shaymin
flavorText: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon ex or Benched Pokemon V. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Cottonee
flavorText: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may heal all damage from your Active Grass Pokemon. If you healed any damage in this way, discard all Energy from that Pokemon.

name: Deerling
flavorText: Deerling have different scents depending on the season. In this form, Deerling have a softly sweet scent that lingers in the nose.
Attack2Text: Discard a Grass Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Sawsbuck
flavorText: Sawsbuck in their Autumn Form are known for having very short tempers. The males fight each other incessantly.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Grubbin
flavorText: Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Grubbin and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Dhelmise
flavorText: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If you have any Metal Pokemon on your Bench, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Bramblin
flavorText: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.

name: Brambleghast
flavorText: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokemon will bury an entire town.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon gets +50 HP for each Prize card your opponent has taken.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokemon. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Scovillain ex
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand. Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Rellor
flavorText: It rolls its mud ball around while the energy it needs for evolution matures. Eventually the time comes for it to evolve.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Rabsca
flavorText: An infant sleeps inside the ball. Rabsca rolls the ball soothingly with its legs to ensure the infant sleeps comfortably.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage from and effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokemon done to your Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Iron Leaves ex
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may switch it with your Active Pokemon. If you do, you may move any amount of Energy from your other Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: It can't run properly when it's newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Energy card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: This Pokemon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Slugma
flavorText: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Burned, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Magcargo
flavorText: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent's Active Pokemon moves to the Bench during their turn, their new Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokemon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 6 cards.
Attack2Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Heatmor
flavorText: There's a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokemon will fall ill.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. For each tails, discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Litten
flavorText: It spends even the smallest amount of downtime grooming its fur with its tongue. Loose fur gathers in its stomach and serves as fuel for fiery moves.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Torracat
flavorText: In the midst of battle, the fire pouch on Torracat's neck rings like a bell and produces stronger flames than usual.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Flare Strike.

name: Incineroar ex
Ability1Text: Attacks used by this Pokemon cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Turtonator
flavorText: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Sizzlipede
flavorText: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Centiskorch
flavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon isn't Burned, this attack does nothing.

name: Gouging Fire ex
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Blaze Blitz again until it leaves the Active Spot.

name: Totodile
flavorText: It is small but rough and tough. It won't hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Croconaw
flavorText: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Feraligatr
flavorText: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 5 damage counters on this Pokemon. If you do, during this turn, attacks used by this Pokemon do 120 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Giant Wave.

name: Carvanha
flavorText: It won't attack while it's alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the Pokemon attack as a group.

name: Sharpedo
flavorText: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Keldeo
flavorText: Keldeo has strengthened its resolve for battle, filling its body with power and changing its form.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Snom
flavorText: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft, freshly fallen snow, so it will eat its way up a mountain, aiming for the peak.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Frosmoth
flavorText: Frosmoth senses air currents with its antennae. It sends its scales drifting on frigid air, making them fall like snow.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't attack.

name: Wiglett
flavorText: This Pokemon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Finizen
flavorText: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

name: Palafin
flavorText: This Pokemon's ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself for each damage counter on it.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

name: Walking Wake ex
Ability1Text: Damage from attacks used by this Pokemon isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When several of these Pokemon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Raichu
flavorText: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to each Pokemon that has any damage counters on it (both yours and your opponent's), except for this Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokemon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

name: Electivire
flavorText: The amount of electrical energy this Pokemon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has any Water Pokemon in play, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Charjabug
flavorText: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

name: Vikavolt
flavorText: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.
Attack2Text: This attack does 80 more damage for each of your Benched Charjabug.

name: Zeraora
flavorText: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Yamper
flavorText: This Pokemon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Boltund
flavorText: This Pokemon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Lightning Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Wugtrio ex
Attack1Text: Discard up to 3 Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon for each Energy card you discarded in this way. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Iron Hands
flavorText: This Pokemon shares many similarities with Iron Hands, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon ex or Pokemon V, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Iron Thorns
flavorText: Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as Iron Thorns.
Attack1Text: Reveal the top 5 cards of your deck. This attack does 70 damage for each Future card you find there. Then, discard those Future cards and shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Mr. Mime
flavorText: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. You may use the effect of a Supporter card you find there as the effect of this attack.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Marill
flavorText: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Azumarill
flavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Girafarig
flavorText: Girafarig's tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokemon from behind.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Latias
flavorText: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Psychic Pokemon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: In ages past, this Pokemon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Pokemon from their hand to evolve their Pokemon.

name: Solosis
flavorText: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Duosion
flavorText: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mile—but only if its two brains can agree with each other.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokemon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 8 cards of your deck. You may put any number of Pokemon you find there onto your Bench. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Elgyem
flavorText: If this Pokemon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Beheeyem
flavorText: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokemon in play.

name: Cutiefly
flavorText: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. You can find Cutiefly hovering around Gossifleur, trying to get some of Gossifleur's pollen.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Ribombee
flavorText: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs' effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, if the Defending Pokemon is Knocked Out, take 2 more Prize cards.

name: Scream Tail
flavorText: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokemon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.
Attack1Text: Heal 100 damage from 1 of your Benched Ancient Pokemon.

name: Flutter Mane
flavorText: This Pokemon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane, a creature mentioned in a certain book.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Active Pokemon has no Abilities, except for Midnight Fluttering.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Iron Valiant
flavorText: It's possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Zen Blade.

name: Iron Valiant
flavorText: It's possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.
Attack2Text: If you played a Future Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Iron Crown ex
Ability1Text: Attacks used by your Future Pokemon, except any Iron Crown ex, do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on those Pokemon.

name: Meditite
flavorText: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

name: Medicham
flavorText: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

name: Relicanth
flavorText: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokemon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.
Ability1Text: Each of your evolved Pokemon can use any attack from its previous Evolutions. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

name: Drilbur
flavorText: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 Basic Fighting Energy cards and discard them. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Excadrill
flavorText: It's not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill's rampant digging.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Golett
flavorText: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks.

name: Golurk
flavorText: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon ex or Pokemon V, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: This Pokemon is very friendly when it's young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Mudbray
flavorText: This Pokemon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won't dry out even if it's exposed to the sun for a long time.

name: Mudsdale
flavorText: This Pokemon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.
Attack1Text: Attach a Basic Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to each of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 40 damage to itself.

name: Rolycoly
flavorText: On sunny days, Rolycoly will come out onto grassy plains and roll around. Then it will eat the grass that gets tangled in its wheel-like leg.

name: Carkol
flavorText: The temperature inside its body increases when it experiences strong emotions. It rolls around frantically while spewing flames.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Coalossal
flavorText: To intimidate its opponents, Coalossal will vigorously shake its body, scattering coal from its smoldering back.
Attack1Text: This attack does 80 more damage for each Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Great Tusk
flavorText: Sightings of this Pokemon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.
Attack2Text: If your Benched Pokemon have any damage counters on them, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Great Tusk
flavorText: Sightings of this Pokemon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck. If you played an Ancient Supporter card from your hand during this turn, discard 3 more cards in this way.

name: Sandy Shocks
flavorText: No records exist of this Pokemon being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokemon's traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.
Attack1Text: If you have 3 or more Energy in play, this attack does 70 more damage. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

name: Iron Boulder ex
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 8 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Ekans
flavorText: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Arbok
flavorText: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.

name: Gastly
flavorText: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Haunter
flavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Gengar ex
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokemon, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon.
Attack1Text: You may move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon to 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Poochyena
flavorText: A Pokemon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Mightyena
flavorText: It will always obey the commands of a skilled Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.
Attack1Text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokemon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokemon.)

name: Sableye
flavorText: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.
Attack2Text: You may move any number of damage counters from your opponent's Benched Pokemon to their Active Pokemon.

name: Farigiraf ex
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Basic Pokemon ex.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Roaring Moon
flavorText: It is possible that this is the creature listed as Roaring Moon in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Ancient card in your discard pile.

name: Forretress
flavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 40 damage to itself.

name: Scizor ex
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Discard up to 2 Metal Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Mawile
flavorText: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.
Attack1Text: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon to the Active Spot. This attack does 30 damage to the new Active Pokemon.

name: Beldum
flavorText: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum's sharp claws.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Metang
flavorText: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 4 cards of your deck and attach any number of Basic Metal Energy cards you find there to your Pokemon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards and put them on the bottom of your deck.

name: Metagross
flavorText: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokemon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Meteor Mash attack does 60 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Meltan
flavorText: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

name: Melmetal
flavorText: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

name: Iron Treads
flavorText: Sightings of this Pokemon have occurred in recent years. It resembles a mysterious object described in an old expedition journal.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon has a Future Booster Energy Capsule attached, it is Fighting and Metal type.
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Koraidon
flavorText: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Ancient Pokemon in play.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Koraidon ex
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 60 damage to itself.

name: Miraidon
flavorText: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards and attach them to your Future Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Miraidon ex
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Cyber Drive.

name: Raging Bolt ex
Attack1Text: Discard your hand and draw 6 cards.
Attack2Text: You may discard any amount of Basic Energy from your Pokemon. This attack does 70 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: If this Pokemon's sticky saliva gets on you and you don't clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won't go away, either.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Put up to 2 Basic Pokemon you find there onto your opponent's Bench.

name: Lickilicky
flavorText: Lickilicky's strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky's tongue can stretch so far.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

name: Hoothoot
flavorText: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

name: Noctowl
flavorText: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.
Attack1Text: You may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Dunsparce
flavorText: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Dudunsparce
flavorText: This Pokemon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards. If you drew any cards in this way, shuffle this Pokemon and all attached cards into your deck.

name: Skitty
flavorText: It can't stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Delcatty
flavorText: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: You may move any amount of Energy from your Pokemon to your other Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Chatot
flavorText: It mimics the cries of other Pokemon to trick them into thinking it's one of them. This way they won't attack it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Pidove
flavorText: Where people go, these Pokemon follow. If you're scattering food for them, be careful— several hundred of them can gather at once.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon's remaining HP is 30 or less, you may search your deck for an Unfezant or Unfezant ex and put it onto this Pidove to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Tranquill
flavorText: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Unfezant
flavorText: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.
Attack1Text: You may put 2 Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon into their hand.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Minccino
flavorText: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.
Attack2Text: Discard up to 2 Pokemon Tools from your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Cinccino
flavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokemon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.
Attack2Text: This attack does 70 damage for each Special Energy card attached to this Pokemon.

name: Drampa
flavorText: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.
Attack2Text: If all of your Benched Pokemon have at least 1 damage counter on them, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Iron Jugulis
flavorText: It's possible that Iron Jugulis, an object described in an old book, may actually be this Pokemon.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.

name: Shiftry
flavorText: A Pokemon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.
Attack1Text: Choose 3 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. If you do, shuffle all of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that you didn't choose, and all cards attached to those Pokemon, into their deck.
Attack2Text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Grotle
flavorText: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Deerling
flavorText: Deerling have different scents depending on the season. In this form, Deerling have a softly sweet scent that lingers in the nose.
Attack2Text: Discard a Grass Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Sawsbuck
flavorText: Sawsbuck in their Autumn Form are known for having very short tempers. The males fight each other incessantly.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Litten
flavorText: It spends even the smallest amount of downtime grooming its fur with its tongue. Loose fur gathers in its stomach and serves as fuel for fiery moves.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Snom
flavorText: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft, freshly fallen snow, so it will eat its way up a mountain, aiming for the peak.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Charjabug
flavorText: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Psychic Pokemon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokemon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 8 cards of your deck. You may put any number of Pokemon you find there onto your Bench. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Cutiefly
flavorText: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. You can find Cutiefly hovering around Gossifleur, trying to get some of Gossifleur's pollen.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Relicanth
flavorText: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokemon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.
Ability1Text: Each of your evolved Pokemon can use any attack from its previous Evolutions. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

name: Excadrill
flavorText: It's not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill's rampant digging.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Mudsdale
flavorText: This Pokemon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.
Attack1Text: Attach a Basic Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to each of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 40 damage to itself.

name: Arbok
flavorText: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.

name: Gastly
flavorText: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Metagross
flavorText: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokemon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Meteor Mash attack does 60 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Meltan
flavorText: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: If this Pokemon's sticky saliva gets on you and you don't clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won't go away, either.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Put up to 2 Basic Pokemon you find there onto your opponent's Bench.

Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

Attack2Text: Discard up to 2 Pokemon Tools from your opponent's Pokemon.

Attack2Text: This attack does 70 damage for each Special Energy card attached to this Pokemon.

name: Drampa
flavorText: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.
Attack2Text: If all of your Benched Pokemon have at least 1 damage counter on them, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Torterra ex
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Grass Pokemon in play.
Attack2Text: Heal 50 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Iron Leaves ex
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may switch it with your Active Pokemon. If you do, you may move any amount of Energy from your other Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Incineroar ex
Ability1Text: Attacks used by this Pokemon cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Gouging Fire ex
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Blaze Blitz again until it leaves the Active Spot.

name: Walking Wake ex
Ability1Text: Damage from attacks used by this Pokemon isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Wugtrio ex
Attack1Text: Discard up to 3 Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon for each Energy card you discarded in this way. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Iron Crown ex
Ability1Text: Attacks used by your Future Pokemon, except any Iron Crown ex, do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on those Pokemon.

name: Iron Boulder ex
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 8 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Gengar ex
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from their hand to 1 of their Pokemon, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon.
Attack1Text: You may move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon to 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Farigiraf ex
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Basic Pokemon ex.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Scizor ex
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Discard up to 2 Metal Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

Attack2Text: You may discard any amount of Basic Energy from your Pokemon. This attack does 70 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
